At the time of referral and initial screening, the participant had a clinical diagnosis of MCI. The cause was still unclear, and the latest clinic note said AD was the most likely cause, though other causes were not ruled out. Screening MRI was delayed due to needing to obtain low B12 screening follow-up labs. During this time, the participant had another clinic visit with the referring physician on 4/6/2022, who at that time noted interim development of RBD sx, "feeling of presence" hallucinations, and mild visual disturbances. Etiology was then changed to be likely due to Lewy Body disease. This appointment/etiology change was not known by the study team until PI eligibility review, when the EMR was again reviewed. At this point it was determined the pt. was no longer eligible due to a non-AD diagnosis.
